Abortion should not be completely banned, I feel that it should be made to which you can't be far along at all or you shouldn't be allowed to do it. I just find that telling a woman what to do with her body is beyond outrageous. If a woman is raped or forced into sex and gets pregnant and they make abortion illegal. A woman is going to do all sorts of things to make it happen, going as far as trying to miscarry or finding someone to help them and cause major problems. The world would turn into having so many black markets doing illegal, unsafe abortions, possibly even killing the women. 
I don't see any good outcome to abortion being completely banned. I am for a woman having a voice and it is her body, her choice. 
I find quite a few men are trying to ban abortion, these men don't know what it is like to be a woman. Men would not like for a women to tell them what to do with their bodies. Why do they feel it is ok, to make a decision for a women? 
You are taking a womens rights away from her. 
As for birth control, I feel this should not be taken away as well. Some women and young girls are put on birth control, because they have problems with their menstrual cycle. Birth control is used for more than just not getting pregnant. The men trying to ban it know nothing about this. They are just wanting control. NO man should be in control of any womens bodies. 
There are so many things that can help a women with her choice on rather to get an abortion, instead of banning abortion, how about making more help available to get therapy or help support her and encourage her that if she has the baby there will be a support group behind her. 
So many options and choices for help for a women to be had, besides just going straight to banning abortions. 
Lets get together as a whole and do more to prevent unwanted pregnancies and more support for women that are thinking about abortions. Make easier ways and grants etc for women to do adoption, so that way their only option isn't just having an abortion.
